Kohl’s, J.C. Penney and L Brands were the latest mall-based retailers to report declining holiday sales, reinforcing concerns that department stores and apparel chains are losing ground despite robust growth in consumer spending. Shares of the three companies fell in early trading. Key insights Market reaction Kohl’s shares fell 5.8% to $46.50 at 7:50 a.m. in New York early trading. L Brands stock declined 3.6% to $17.31, while J.C. Penney dropped 3.3% to $1.16. © 2020 Bloomberg